{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Hazelnut chocolate spread","content":["Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and mill <b>35 sec\/speed 9<b> or until a fine consistency. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add remaining hazelnut chocolate spread ingredients and blend <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and blend <b>1 min\/speed 6<b> or until a smooth consistency is achieved. Transfer into a sealable jar or container and place into refrigerator until ready to use. Spread will thicken slightly in the refrigerator. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Cupcakes","content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Line a 12-hole muffin tray with paper cases and set aside.","Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and mill <b>25 sec\/speed 9<b> or until finely ground.","Add buckwheat flour, cacao, baking powder and stevia extract (optional) and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil, syrup, eggs, milk and 100 g of the Hazelnut chocolate spread and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and if needed mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>, until well combined. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Pour mixture into prepared paper cases and bake for 15-17 minutes (160°C), until mostly cooked through, but still slightly fudgy in the centre. Allow to cool in tin for 10 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Icing","content":["Place avocado, syrup, cacao and 80 g of the Hazelnut chocolate spread into mixing bowl and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b> or until well combined and smooth.","Spread icing onto cooled cupcakes before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Hazelnut chocolate spread","content":["150 g raw hazelnuts, skins on","40 g raw cacao powder","100 g pure maple syrup","100 g full cream milk"]},{"title":"Cupcakes","content":["130 g raw hazelnuts, skins on","60 g buckwheat flour (see Tips)","40 g raw cacao powder (see Tips)","2 tsp baking powder (see Tips)","&frac18; tsp stevia extract powder (optional)","70 g extra virgin olive oil","120 g pure maple syrup","2 eggs","80 g milk","100 g hazelnut chocolate spread (see Tips)"]},{"title":"Icing","content":["1 avocado, ripe, flesh only","90 g pure maple syrup","30 g raw cacao powder","80 g hazelnut chocolate spread (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r122148","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-AHmTNXcpCrA\/XZWqyqZK-OI\/AAAAAAAAfdc\/HG9cZt0klBAcAmkwEvvRPfIIVeiwGfMZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_UZl9Coa3gl7Ue3GJ.png","title":"Chocolate cupcakes with chocolate avocado icing","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.3 g","fat":"22.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"15.7 g","calories":"1224 kJ \/ 291 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable storage jar or container, 12-hole muffin tray, 12 cupcake liners, wire rack, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This hazelnut chocolate spread can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks, but no longer than the use by date of the milk you use.","If you don’t have any raw cacao on hand, you can use regular cocoa powder instead.","If you would prefer a lower fructose option, you can substitute the maple syrup with rice malt syrup. You can also use activated or roasted hazelnuts instead of raw, if preferred.","You can make your own buckwheat flour in your Thermomix from scratch. Place 250 g raw buckwheat groats into your mixing bowl and mill <strong>2 min\/speed 10<\/strong>, until a fine, flour-like consistency is achieved.","If you’re making these cupcakes for someone with a wheat intolerance, then choose a gluten-free brand of baking powder. All the remaining ingredients are gluten free.","You can use homemade or store-bought hazelnut chocolate spread for this recipe. Homemade spread is the much healthier option. Store-bought spreads tend to be sweeter, so you’re unlikely to need the stevia extract powder in the cupcake mixture if using.","The avocado in the icing adds some green raw goodness to these cupcakes, with a boost of Vitamin C, folate, Vitamin K, Vitamin E, fibre and potassium. The flavour is quite subtle - it is a great way to get some extra green into your day."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","12 portions"]}